The paper deals with rate allocation in a fading Gaussian multiple-access channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The proposed rate allocation policy is designed to maximize a utility function, which involves optimization (cs.SY) techniques. The paper also analyzes the effect of temporal channel variations on the policy's performance, which involves signal processing (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts.
